# Caddy terminates TLS (automatic Let's Encrypt for a real domain) and proxies
# to the app. This is what removes the cert-trust friction during a PoV:
# the gateway sees a publicly-trusted HTTPS endpoint.
#
# For a local/lab demo set DCSIM_DOMAIN=localhost — Caddy issues an internal cert.
#
# Served on 443 (all DC types) AND 9440: CloudGuard's Nutanix connector hardcodes Prism Central's
# port 9440 and its Hostname field rejects a scheme/port, so the portal must answer on 9440 with the
# same cert for Nutanix Test Connection to reach it. Caddy serves the same site on both ports.

{$DCSIM_DOMAIN}, {$DCSIM_DOMAIN}:9440 {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy app:8000
}
